               <p>JOHN AUGUSTUS HALCOMB. I live in <placeName id="t18260216-137-crimeloc731">Diana-place, New-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260216-137-crimeloc731" type="placeName" value="Diana-place, New-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260216-137-crimeloc731" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260216-137-off729 t18260216-137-crimeloc731"></join> - I let a furnished room to the female prisoner, about the 18th of January - her husband called the next day, and settled about it; when I was out they came in - these articles are part of the furniture; they left me on Saturday, the 28th of January, without notice. I found them afterwards, and gave charge of them. I received some duplicates, in a letter, of the goods, pawned at Mr. Wadmore's.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by Mr. CRESWELL. Q. Does that letter purport to come from the male prisoner? A. Yes, and he stated so when I took him into custody.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260216-137-person901">
                  HENRY 
                  GEORGE WALLIS
               <interp inst="t18260216-137-person901" type="surname" value="GEORGE WALLIS"></interp>
